{"ts":"2026-06-27T01:46:32.857Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing Layout Behavior**\n\nI've realized the `isAuthPage` check is missing in `AdminPortalLayout`, a critical detail! This means `/admin` and `/admin/login` will render with the app shell, contrary to expectations. The missing conditional logic renders the layout *around* the auth pages, which is an error. We need to mirror the bypass from the `/portal/layout.tsx` for these admin authentication flows. This ensures clean, unencumbered auth pages.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T01:46:34.290Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Refining Redirection Logic**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the redirection logic within `/app/admin/page.tsx`. I see that `/admin` immediately pushes to `/admin/dashboard`, which is a problem if the user isn't authenticated yet. This means we're redirecting users to a protected area without any prior auth check! We need to make sure auth checks happen *before* the redirect; otherwise, the initial auth page may flash, or we'll have an infinite redirect loop. I have some ideas on how to fix this redirection flow.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T01:46:36.134Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Clarifying Portal Entry Points**\n\nI'm now clarifying the entry point logic. I've confirmed that `/admin` should function as the Admin Portal entry and render the login interface directly, analogous to `/portal`. This is consistent with explicit route creation requirements. I'm aligning `/admin` to render `<SecureLogin defaultRole=\"Administrator\" />`, which solves the `/admin/login` question. I see both `/admin` and `/admin/login` will present the login screen.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
